# Cross-platform line endings.
# Shell scripts MUST stay LF. A Windows stand-in runs them under Git Bash/WSL,
# and vm-up.sh uploads startup-script.sh to a Linux VM — CRLF there breaks the
# shebang and the VM won't boot. (After adding this file, run
# `git add --renormalize .` once so already-committed files are stored as LF.)
*.sh text eol=lf

# Other text executed on Linux / parsed cross-platform
*.py text eol=lf
*.yml text eol=lf
*.yaml text eol=lf
